@startuml
participant "UserA " as C
participant "ndnsd-locator \n (d1)" as SL
participant "ndnsd-publisher \n (d2)" as SP
participant "UserB " as P

skinparam SequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam style strictuml

P -> SP: publish service \n (type: printers, \n name: \n /printer1/service-info)
SP -> P: status code \n (success \n or failed callback)

note over SP, SL #white
nodes sync with each
other in the background
end note

C -> SL: request service \n (e.g. printers)
SL -> SL: Get service names \n {/printer1/service-info} via sync

SL -> SP: Interest (**I**): /printer1/service-info


SP -> SL: Data (**D**) : \n name = /printer1/service-info \n content: "HP ledger jet"
SL -> C: send response \n (service info/status)
@enduml
